https://github.com/ethereum-cdap/cohort-one/blob/master/development-updates.md

You are highly encouraged to do them and do them regularly.  It's not something that will "just happen" and you will benefit from taking the time to do them.

- They help you practice your technical writing skills which are paramount to success in this ecosystem.
- They force you to organize your thoughts.  
- If you can't explain something you probably don't understand it.
- At the end of the program they will serve as a solid record of the your progress and work.  This is valuable if you are hoping to find a job at the end of this....
- They help others who are working alongside you and who will come along after you.

If you've been working for more than two weeks without publishing something..... maybe pause what you are doing and take some time to write something before you continue with the "code stuff"?
